[MUSIC]

2
00:00:08.047 --> 00:00:12.161
Hello, welcome to HSK Chinese.

3
00:00:12.161 --> 00:00:17.089
[Nǐ hǎo！Huānyínɡ láidào HSK hànyǔ kètánɡ.]

4
00:00:17.089 --> 00:00:22.369
[Wǒ jiào Yú Bīn. Hěn ɡāoxìnɡ rènshi nǐ.] 

5
00:00:22.369 --> 00:00:26.945
[Nǐ jiào shénme mínɡzi？] 

6
00:00:26.945 --> 00:00:34.690
[Nǐ shì nǎ ɡuó rén?] Today we are going to learn how to ask about nationality in Chinese.

7
00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:44.830
Where are you from or
what's your nationality, is [Nǐ shì nǎ ɡuó rén?].

8
00:00:44.830 --> 00:00:52.315
In Chinese [shì] is to be,
[nǎ] is which.

9
00:00:52.315 --> 00:00:56.408
[ɡuó] means country or nation.

10
00:00:56.408 --> 00:00:59.950
[rén] is person or people.

11
00:00:59.950 --> 00:01:07.049
Word by word is,
you are which country person.

12
00:01:07.049 --> 00:01:10.983
Read after me please.

13
00:01:10.983 --> 00:01:16.292
[FOREIGN] Does the word

14
00:01:16.292 --> 00:01:24.400
order in the sentence weird? Not really!

15
00:01:25.530 --> 00:01:30.658
It's the same as [Nǐ jiào shénme míngzi?] a subject,

16
00:01:30.658 --> 00:01:36.290
a verb, a question word, and a noun.

17
00:01:38.540 --> 00:01:42.259
If you ask me [Nǐ shì nǎ ɡuórén?]

18
00:01:42.259 --> 00:01:47.610
I will tell you [Wǒ shì Zhōnɡɡuórén.]

19
00:01:47.610 --> 00:01:50.167
I'm Chinese.

20
00:01:50.167 --> 00:01:54.363
[Zhōnɡɡuó] is China.

21
00:01:54.363 --> 00:02:02.773
So to talk about nationality in Chinese
you just add ren after the name of the country.

22
00:02:02.773 --> 00:02:07.643
For example, American is [Měiɡuórén].

23
00:02:07.643 --> 00:02:13.237
Japanese is [Rìběnrén].

24
00:02:13.237 --> 00:02:16.494
Please pay attention to [shì].

25
00:02:16.494 --> 00:02:21.425
Chinese verbs do not have inflections,

26
00:02:21.425 --> 00:02:26.210
that is, the form of the verb is the same,

27
00:02:26.210 --> 00:02:29.991
no matter what the subject is.

28
00:02:29.991 --> 00:02:33.688
For example,

29
00:02:33.688 --> 00:02:40.774
in the sentences, [FOREIGN]

30
00:02:40.774 --> 00:02:47.552
the verb is always [shì]

31
00:02:47.552 --> 00:02:51.873
never changes.

32
00:02:51.873 --> 00:02:56.305
Read after me please.

33
00:02:56.305 --> 00:03:03.327
[FOREIGN]

34
00:03:03.327 --> 00:03:10.349
again,

35
