56
00:04:59.345 --> 00:05:01.524
[tā] means she.

57
00:05:01.524 --> 00:05:04.775
[yě] means also.

58
00:05:04.775 --> 00:05:09.470
The question is, where is she from?

59
00:05:09.470 --> 00:05:14.973
And Xudong said, she is also Chinese.

60
00:05:14.973 --> 00:05:17.245
Different from English,

61
00:05:17.245 --> 00:05:21.029
[yě] is placed before a verb.

62
00:05:21.029 --> 00:05:27.419
You can't put it after a verb or
at the end of a sentence.

63
00:05:27.419 --> 00:05:30.788
Moreover, if you say [Me too.]

64
00:05:30.788 --> 00:05:36.989
You can't say [wǒ yě] but [wǒ yě shì].

